storyInfo: The misery of the citizens of Sal Viento stirs Senshi's desire to cook a bounteous feast for them. However, a local priest of the Church of the Deep has other plans. Gazing towards a distant cave overrun by the Seaborn, a scheme comes to mind.

attributes.content: In their swift fall downwards, the hunters look just like—
—Shooting stars.
A sight that those who live in the deep seas rarely have the opportunity to witness.
With his desires and plans clouding his head, the bishop has, of course, never looked up at the night sky to enjoy that spectacle.
But they are different.

When the Abyssal Hunters had to fight for their lives and escape from the melancholy and sacrifice, they swam upwards, and when they finally reached the surface, they could only solemnly gaze upon the star-filled night sky...
The Hunters have all etched the destinies of these short-lived stars into their hearts.
Despite everything, the darkness can still be broken.
Now die.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Three shooting stars illuminate the deep passageway.
The bishop is horrified. But because it has neither lungs nor vocal tracts, this thundering sound is as close as it gets to a scream for its current body.

Amidst the debris and crumbling walls, the monster's bloated, dying form sprawls across much of the karst cave. Once emanating a strange, eerie beauty, its bizarre body now begins to stiffen in dread as it faces impending doom.

attributes.text: The bishop is dead, and he will be forgotten completely.

attributes.content: This is bad.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: There's not a single living thing outside this city.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: I don't think we're going to be able to restock our supplies here.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Anyone find anything?
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Nothing on my end. The folks in the other parts of the city won't say a word either.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: They react when they see food, but won't answer any of my questions.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: Don't even bother asking them for supplies. I've been giving out bits of whatever rations I had on me.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: Things were mostly the same for me. The only word that comes to mind when I look at these houses is 'miserable.'
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Hard to imagine how the locals can even live here.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Aye, I've searched a few markets. Seems they're all long-abandoned.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: Safe to say most people here haven't had a good meal in a long while.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: Breaks my heart.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: Yeah...
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: I followed someone to the coast, thinking I could find something there, but...
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: Hrrh... Hrrh...
attributes.name: Townsfolk A

attributes.content: He's just like the others, wandering aimlessly on the beach and sometimes digging through sand, as if there's food buried beneath.
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: Hungry...
attributes.name: Townsfolk B

attributes.content: Fins, shells, can eat.
attributes.name: Townsfolk A

attributes.content: Eat, eat.
attributes.name: Townsfolk A

attributes.content: Senshi lays down his axe and nimbly makes his way in front of the pair, opening up the bundles they are carrying.
Within are piles of finbeasts and shells scavenged from the beach, but from the foul odor they emit, it's clear they've begun to rot.
Though the two seem barely conscious, they begin to stuff the putrefying food into their mouths, overcome by some primal fear of Senshi stealing their meal.
Oh. That's rather...
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: That's... just sad...
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: Since there's nothing here that's of help, we should get out of here, quick.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: Their customs are far too strange, and I don't think they're particularly friendly either...
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: This is just my guess.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: The locals here haven't had a proper meal for too long. This led to them gradually growing numb to their surroundings.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: If we make 'em something good to eat, maybe it'll bring them back to their senses, even if just a bit.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: Seriously?
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: It's true. It's normal that you don't know this, but starvation and stress will slowly make you lose yourself.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: Sounds like you're talking from experience.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: If possible, I was hoping we could at least fill their bellies with a proper meal.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: I don't mind the idea, but we need to find food for ourselves first. If not, we won't get very far. Right, Chilchuck?
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Yeah, I suppose.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: But let's make one thing clear. The reason we lost our supplies in the first place is because you all went crazy and wandered off in Sami, so don't expect me to do everything this time too!
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: Well, naturally.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Weary travelers, do you seek... sustenance?
Wait, you can understand us?
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: Yes.
Great! We—
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: Wait, Marcille. Don't you find it strange that he can when everyone else can't?
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: It is natural for you to be wary.
But fear not. I have come to offer you guidance.
Who the hell are you?
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: I am an itinerant priest, bringing the teachings of the sea to the masses.
What of you? You do not seem like Iberians. What brings you to Sal Viento?
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: We're looking to resupply for our journey.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: I presume you have not made much progress on that?
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: No matter. Since we are here, we will not see you starve.
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: Yes. We are the church taking care of this city. All under our eaves are brethren.
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: Though you may be outsiders, if you are willing to follow our guidance, you too may join us.
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: We would not allow our own to go hungry.
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: (Sounds pretty shady...)
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: If we go with him to find food, won't this mean the townspeople can have a decent meal as well?
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Don't say that like you're actually thinking of joining his kooky cult!
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: *cackle* The ocean's blessing is boundless. It will not mind sharing a sliver with you.
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: But, it is only for the strong and worthy.
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: What do you mean?
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: I bet it means he knows where the food is, but not everyone can make it out alive.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: That is one way to interpret it.
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: I wouldn’t want to influence you into danger, it’s just—
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: Just tell us where it is. We're experienced adventurers. We can handle a little danger.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: If you say so. Follow the coastline south. There will be a cave.
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: What you seek is within.
attributes.name: Priest

attributes.content: There's something fishy about that guy, Laios.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Then why'd you listen to him?
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: I have a hunch that whatever weird's going on in town is connected to the church he was talking about.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: If we follow his 'guidance', it should lead us to something.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Besides, if there's an ambush waiting for us, I'm sure you'll notice beforehand!
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Well, I guess you're right...
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: Hmm? That's—
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: A kraken! It's huge!
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Laios, look out!
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: Calm down. I don't think it's moving any time soon.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: Eh! It's already dead?
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: Wow! A kraken this huge... The church wasn't lying to us!
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Look at its tentacles, its suckers, its sea anemone-like organs! This must be its... head?
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: I'd love to see what it looked like alive. It should be about the size of a tower and would've looked impressive.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Though it does taste rather nasty...
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: This isn't a kraken, though maybe they share a common ancestor.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: My stomach's starting to hurt from going hungry...
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Still, you shouldn't just eat things you know nothing about!
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: I agree, we shouldn't.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: Eh?
attributes.name: Chilchuck & Marcille

attributes.content: Sea creatures can contain toxins after their death. Take crabs, for example. They can be contaminated by harmful bacteria, even if they haven't been dead for long.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: If you really want to eat something...
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: We can see if there are any parasites still alive in there!
attributes.name: Senshi & Laios

attributes.content: Gah! I shouldn't have gotten them started!
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: I've learned to just say nothing in times like these.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: I do wonder though, who killed this giant creature? It must have been hard avoiding these tentacles...
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Laios, hush. I hear something...
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: Marcille uses a stick to hoist a gooey, fluorescent... thing.
Eww... I feel kinda sick just looking at it.
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: It glows, even during the day... It's beautiful...
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Absolutely not! I'm gonna throw it away!
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: What a waste... Say, what's that you threw it on?
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: What is that?
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Ah!
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Is something wrong?
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: Laios, watch your step!
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: Oh! Seagrass?
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Careful, lad. I don't think it's a good idea to step on it.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: Hmm? Now that you mention it... I do feel a bit numb all over.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Avoid the seagrass as best you can, guys!
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: You say that, but there aren't many other places we can stand.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: It looks like all the plants in this cave were actually monsters, huh?
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: There's no doubt about it. We're in the kraken's lair.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Which means all these things coming out from deeper in the cave must've lived alongside it.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Which means...
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: Fresh ingredients!
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Marcille, can you use magic on the seagrass? Set it on fire, or something?
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: Are you crazy?! If we make a fire, wouldn't that be like shouting 'Hey, over here!' to all the monsters?
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: Yeah, which is exactly why we're doing it.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: The seagrass is spreading out from the depths of the cave. If we chased them in, we'd be at a disadvantage.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Better to use a fire and let them come to us.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Sounds like you really thought this through.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: Don't worry, we're not going to take them head on. You can wait outside. Once we've gotten enough ingredients, we'll get out.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: And if something does happen, you can come to our rescue.
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: Hmph. Whatever.
attributes.name: Chilchuck

attributes.content: He must be going through a rebellious phase.
attributes.name: Senshi

attributes.content: On a separate note, haven't you considered the remote possibility that I might not play along?
attributes.name: Marcille

attributes.content: Eh?
attributes.name: Laios

attributes.content: From his expression, Marcille can tell that he never even considered she wouldn't.
*sigh* Fine. Cover your ears.
attributes.name: Marcille
